Offer: 2-Chiropractic Adjustments with Consultation for 1 Person
Details: Chiropractic, a branch of healthcare that focuses on the musculoskeletal and nervous systems, treats physical ailments including back pain, neck pain, joint aches and headaches. Tap on the expertise and professionalism of Dr. Dylan Altfeld, who has over 16 years of experience in the treatment of injuries, pain, sports performance and recovery, and who received his doctorate from Palmer College of Chiropractic (USA) in 1996, offrting treatments to target afflictions ranging from the normal aches and pains to advanced spinal conditions such as arthritis, bulging discs and facet irritation. He has also treated patients from all walks of life - from infants, to athletes and the elderly.   Using a drug-free, hands-on approach, you will receive a thorough examination and diagnosis of specific physical conditions, before the Doctor will advise on the most effective treatments to counteract these ailments. Depending on his advice, an X-ray may be in order. The doctors on hand aim to figure out just the right method to help you return back to health as quickly as possible. The Gonstead method is practised by the staff, which assesses one’s spinal condition on five dimensions - visualisation, instrumentation, static palpation, motion palpation and X-ray analysis (if indicated). This technique minimises spinal rotations and increases treatment specificity to deliver more effective results.
